esJ_l1b_Ni0.title: Warsaw Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
esJ_l1b_Ni0.description:
Warsaw – The capital of Poland stands today as the product of some of history’s most defining events. Follow us through the city and see all the best spots to visit here. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Warsaw: https://www.expedia.com/Warsaw.d178317.Destination-Travel-Guides

For centuries #Warsaw has been a center of refinement and knowledge. Its strategic position has also made it one of the most invaded countries in Europe. Your #vacation here will bring you up close to the sites of these historic events in the Old Town and across Warsaw’s many monuments to the past. 

Enjoy more historical sites along the Royal Route. Visit St Johns Cathedral and St Anne’s Church, whose interior miraculously survived the war. One of the few statues not destroyed by the German army is the mermaid Syrena, the symbol and protector of Warsaw.

Keep apace of the city’s stories at the many museums here. Visit the Palace of Culture and Science and the Copernicus Science Centre. Don’t miss Wilanow Palace, with luxurious artworks and formal gardens.

Since the fall of the Iron Curtain, Poland’s economy has boomed, reflected in the luxury malls, such as Zlote Tarasy and the VITKAC Department store.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Warsaw: https://www.expedia.com/Warsaw.dx178317

4ZxgBQA7cuY.title: Bolivia Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
4ZxgBQA7cuY.description:
Bolivia – Welcome to the “Rooftop of the World” where you can experience breathtaking landscapes, ancient civilizations and colorful wildlife. Check out the best things to see and do in Bolivia. 
When ready, browse vacation packages to Bolivia: https://www.expedia.com/Bolivia.d21.Destination-Travel-Guides 

A #vacation to #Bolivia, a landlocked South American country, holds the promise of discovery for adventurous souls. While pretty Sucre is Bolivia’s judicial capital, La Paz is its political capital and also its main tourist hub.

Journey high to the Mirador Laikacota for city views. Deep in the valley below #visit the central Plaza Murillo, home to the most precious buildings: the Presidential Palace, National Congress and Metropolitan Cathedral. Stay near the Plaza San Francisco for its proximity to hidden gems, such as the curious Witches’ Market, the Musical Instrument Museum and the Coca Museum.

Bolivia is a diamond in the rough; relatively undeveloped, but extremely authentic, colorful and cultural. Bolivia’s riches shine through in the country’s high altiplanos, its floating reed islands on Lake Titicaca, the silver mines of Potosi, the infinite salt flats of the Salar de Uyuni and the untamed tropical lowlands in the vast Amazon basin.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it.

To manage seats after booking:
• To view your seat assignment, check your confirmation email or your itinerary.
• To select or change your seat, open your itinerary and select Choose Seats under Manage Booking.

qt9Vp0_3bs0.title: Margaret River Wine Region Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
qt9Vp0_3bs0.description:
Margaret River Wine Region – Surrounded by coasts on three sides and enjoying virtually rain-free summers, this region is primed and ready for lovers of more than just wine. 
When ready, browse vacation packages to Margaret River Wine Region: https://www.expedia.com/Margaret-River-Wine-Region.d6046852.Destination-Travel-Guides

A #vacation to the #MargaretRiverWineRegion can take you down the Western Australian coastline for over 80 miles and stretch inland for a further 20. Start your #vacation with one of Australia’s most scenic drives, Caves Road, which gets its name from the limestone caves which honeycomb the region. #Visit the region’s main settlement and cruise from cellar door to cellar door, sampling some of the most exciting Chardonnays, Shirazs and Cabernet Sauvignons on the planet.
 
At Margaret River’s northern end is Cape Naturaliste, a headland surrounded by secluded spots. Between June and December, the lookout points around the lighthouse make this cape a fabulous place to spot whales. #Explore the Cape to Cape track, which follows beaches and cliff tops.
 
Margaret River is one of those rare destinations that’s a feast for the senses, with tastes, sights and sounds you’ll savor, for the rest of your days.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Margaret River Wine Region: https://www.expedia.com/Margaret-River-Wine-Region.dx6046852

ZFo6SdIh7mc.title: Expedia bot for Facebook Messenger
ZFo6SdIh7mc.description:
You can now chat with Expedia on Facebook Messenger for a convenient way to search for hotels options and move forward with booking.  Here's how to get started:

1. Download Messenger on your iOS or Android phone. 
2. To access Messenger on desktop, log into Facebook.com or Messenger.com through your web browser.
3. Open a New Message and type Expedia or @Expedia into the To: field. 
4. From there, tell the bot a bit about the your hotel booking options! This could be things like the city you are going to and the date when you would like to check-in.
5. The Expedia bot will respond with any follow-up questions to better answer your request. 
6. You can always restart the conversation with the Expedia bot by typing “restart”

Learn more at https://viewfinder.expedia.com.

LcKnx7I97yk.title: Dublin Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
LcKnx7I97yk.description:
Dublin – where history and heritage thrive, and good cheer abounds. Check out the top sights and stories of the capital city and start planning a trip of your own!

When ready, browse vacation packages to Dublin: https://www.expedia.com/Dublin.d178256.Destination-Travel-Guides

Despite a long and sometimes tragic history of invasion and resistance, this thriving business capital has poetry, music and literature percolating through its cobblestones.

While #Dublin proudly honours its past, it is equally passionate about enjoying each and every new day. Nowhere is life celebrated more than in the city’s nearly 700 pubs. 

Of all the gifts, Dublin has given to the world, perhaps the most intoxicating are its stories. Originally built for the sons of the Irish gentry, the ivy-covered stone buildings of Trinity College are home to some of the oldest remaining manuscripts in the world, including the 1000-year-old Book of Kells.

Dubliner Jonathan Swift, once said, “May you live all the days of your life.” There is no better way to define Dublin. Its passion for life is contagious, captivating and sure to stay with you after your #vacation here for the rest of your days.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Dublin: https://www.expedia.com/Dublin.dx178256

WhhtTTStsIY.title: How to make the most of sea days on a Disney cruise
WhhtTTStsIY.description:
When booking a cruise, it’s natural think about which ports you’ll visit along the way. But what about sea days? They are the time to unwind, let loose and really enjoy the ship. And when you’re sailing on Disney Cruise Line, you’ll want lots of time to take in everything there is to do onboard. Here are some of our favorite ways to maximize days at sea. Plan your cruise: http://bit.ly/1T5ovZ5

1. Get some pool time
Nothing says vacation like pool time. Adults can visit the Quiet Cove pool which is exclusively for guests 18+. There is a pool bar, infinity edge hot tubs and plenty of lounge space. It’s great for when your kids are in the nursery or kids clubs. When it’s time for the family to come back together, there are also two family-friendly pools, waterslides and water play areas for kids of all ages. And don’t forget the AquaDuck! It’s the first-of-its-kind water coaster at sea taking riders up, down, around and even off the side of the ship before splashing back on deck.

2. Learn something new   
A sea day is also a great time to learn something new. Disney Cruise Line offers everything from cooking demos, towel folding workshops, animation classes, fitness seminars, behind-the-scenes ship tours and more. Adults can get schooled on their favorite cocktails with tasting classes. Check the Disney Cruise Line Navigator app for a dialing listing of onboard activities. 

3. Day-time Entertainment
There’s no shortage of planned activities on sea days. All of the youth clubs have scheduled fun under the care of specially trained Disney counselors. Even the nursery has activities for the little ones! Ever wanted to solve a mystery? The Midship Detective Agency allows you to do just that. This all-ages interactive adventure takes you all around the ship to solve cases with clues, technology and good old-fashioned intuition. You can also challenge yourself to some healthy competition with Disney trivia or get swept up in board game madness. You’ll get so into the action that time will fly. 

4. Night-time Entertainment
When nighttime comes, you can soak up the ambience at onboard entertainment venues. Piano bars let you revel in the sounds of live piano music. At the Skyline bar, you can travel the world in one night as the ‘city views’ change from one international destination to another. There are a myriad of other lounges that offer fun throughout the evening. At the end of the day, take a relaxing stroll around the upper decks and soak in the starlight and sea breezes. You may even meet some new friends along the way!

Want to learn more about Disney Cruise Line? Watch the rest of our Expedia At Disney playlist on YouTube. Also, check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest updates.

YYGVuss3Mn4.title: How to book the perfect Disney Cruise
YYGVuss3Mn4.description:
Booking a cruise should be just as easy as sailing on one. Luckily, we’ve made the planning process easy for you. On Expedia, you can search for cruises by destination, travel dates, trip length and more to find the sailing that works best for you. Plan your cruise: http://bit.ly/1T5ovZ5
 
After you’ve selected your destination and the dates you want to sail, it’s time to pick your stateroom type. You can pick your exact stateroom on Expedia with a virtual map. Inside staterooms offer the best value, but lack exterior views. But on the Disney Dream and Disney Fantasy, inside staterooms feature a magical porthole which showcases real-time views of the sea and virtual sightings of animated Disney characters. Outside staterooms are also available, offering two portholes or one large porthole. Verandah staterooms, which offer private balconies, provide you with the ultimate setting to enjoy refreshing sea breezes. Premium suites are also available, which gives you the ultimate luxury. Many staterooms sleep up to 5 people. A fold-out couch and pull-down beds help maximize the space. Most staterooms also offer split bathrooms. One bathroom has a toilet and sink, while the other has a shower and sink. This makes it easy for larger parties to get ready in the morning. 
 
While counting down to your cruise, check out the Disney Cruise Line website to pre-book spa appointments, premium dining, port adventures and more. Once the planning is done, you don’t have to worry about a thing onboard. From spending time with the ones you love to watching the only fireworks at sea, there are endless reasons to book a Disney Cruise. 

Want to learn more about Disney Cruise Line? Watch the rest of our Expedia At Disney playlist on YouTube. Also, check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest updates.

UijZfDe8ZKY.title: How to stay healthy on a Disney cruise
UijZfDe8ZKY.description:
Cruising is all about indulgences. And on a Disney Cruise, there’s no shortage of great food! But there’s no reason why you can’t stay ship shape as well. Here are the top 10 ways to stay healthy on a Disney cruise. Plan your cruise: http://bit.ly/1T5ovZ5

1. Shuffleboard
Enjoy a round of shuffleboard on the lower deck of the ship. It’s the perfect opportunity to get away from the crowds and breathe in the fresh ocean air. 

2. Goofy’s Sports Deck
This action-packed area allows guests of all ages to play a game of full-court basketball. Make sure to drink plenty of water in the heat!

3. Jogging Track
Each of the Disney ships offers a track for jogging and walking. Hint: 8 laps around the Disney Dream ship equals a 5k.

4. Miniature Golf
If you don’t want to break a series sweat, you can still stay active with a round of mini golf. The course is a prime location for watching the sunset too. 

5. Fitness Center
The gyms onboard Disney ships are state-of-the-art exercise clubs with spectacular ocean views. These adult-only facilities offer everything you need to work out while at sea. Choose from treadmills, weight machines, personal training and fitness classes. 

6. Spa
Taking care of yourself on vacation also means taking time to unwind. Senses Spa offers a variety of treatment options. The Rainforest Room offers the benefits of steam, heat, water therapy and aromatherapy. 

5. Healthy Food Options
When it’s time to refuel, restaurant menus on Disney Cruise Line provide options for those looking to dine on the healthy side.

GOyxqFn3DvE.title: How to find something for everyone on a Disney cruise
GOyxqFn3DvE.description:
Disney Cruise Line is the #1 line for families. Of course, when most people think ‘family,’ they think of the kiddos, but family means something for everyone. That’s just what you’ll find on every Disney ship. Check out our tips for taking advantage of activities and entertainment for all ages while sailing with Disney Cruise Line. Plan your cruise: http://bit.ly/1T5ovZ5

Adults can start their day with a specialty coffee from Cove Café, one of the venues exclusive to guests who are 18+. This coffee shop offers mouth-watering drinks in a plush atmosphere. Afterwards, adults can hit the spa and get pampered with facials, massages, saunas, manicures, pedicures and more. Health nuts can even keep up with their fitness routines at the onboard gym. Or work up a sweat on the jogging track and sports deck. In the evening, adults can watch sports in the pub. Many of the lounges are open during the day, offering activities for all ages. But at night the clubs offer an adult exclusive evening of dancing, comedy, live piano music and more. Our favorite is La Piazza, a lounge inspired by Italy. It even offers a bar modeled after a vintage carousel.

Kids of all ages are welcome on a Disney Cruise. You’re never too young to enjoy fun activities like daily toddler time play groups, the Aqualab water play area and the Wake Up with Disney Jr Dance Party. Also, having a nursery onboard means new parents can enjoy a little time to unwind and spend date nights together. Tweens even have their own space. If your kids are too cool for the kid’s club, but not quite ready for the teen club, then they can spend time at Edge – the youth club designed just for tweens. 

Guests of all ages can enjoy the first-run movies at the onboard movie theater. And there’s D Lounge, a family-friendly entertainment venue with karaoke, trivia, game shows and more. Last but not least, everyone can share over-the-top dinners and broadway style shows nightly. With so many options, there’s something for everyone on a Disney Cruise.

ZksLxjfCE1g.title: How to maximize dining on a Disney cruise
ZksLxjfCE1g.description:
Everyone knows there’s no shortage of food on a cruise. That’s especially true when sailing with Disney Cruise Line. But don’t worry, it’s not all pizza, hot dog and kiddie fare! Guests can enjoy upscale menu items crafted by Michelin star-rated chefs or wine pairings selected by master sommeliers. Out of all the options, here are some of our favorite dining experiences with Disney Cruise Line. Plan your cruise: http://bit.ly/1T5ovZ5

Specialty dining at Remy and Palo
Petites assiettes means “small plates,” and this gem is an experience offered at Remy, a French-inspired fine dining restaurant exclusively for adults. There are six dishes in all, each perfectly paired with wine. The Disney ships are also home to Palo, which is widely regarded as a favorite dining spot. This adult-only venue offers Italian cooking for brunch and dinner. The fan favorite here is the chocolate soufflé, but I think the views are equally scrumptious!

Rotating dining rooms
With Disney Cruise Line you don’t simply dine in the same dining room every evening – you visit one of three uniquely themed family dining spaces each night. You might dine in an enhanted garden that transforms from day to night while you dine or enjoy South American flair at Cariocas. And then there’s our favorite, Animator’s Palate, where Disney characters come to life before your eyes. On the Disney magic and Disney fantasy you can even see your hand-drawn characters become part of the show!

Casual dining options
Or you can simply go casual by grabbing food up on deck. There are healthy wraps and fruit. Also, indulge with complementary soft serve ice cream, soda and coffee. And, yes, there’s pizza, chicken and burgers. But also more exotic items like Shawarma – complete with grilled meats and lots of toppings.

Cabanas buffet
We’re going to let you in on the best kept Disney Cruise dining secret. Imagine you’ve spent an action-packed day exploring Rome, snorkeling in the Caribbean, or simply wore yourself out riding the Aquaduck water coaster, and you’re looking for a laid back, full service dining experience. Then why not skip the dining room and instead opt for dinner under the stars up on deck? Cabanas offers a free-flowing buffet experience by day, but come nighttime it features signature dishes from the main dining restaurants in a subdued, and sublime, setting.

24-hour room service
Not even feeling up to leaving your room to dine at all? No worries, 24-hour in-room dining onboard is also complimentary, meaning that you don’t even need to put on pants to enjoy fresh salmon, salads, paninis, soup and more. It’s the perfect option for late-night snacking, a casual dinner to enjoy with Disney movies in your room, or a daytime meal to savor with breathtaking verandah views.

Whether savoring upscale dining, snacking on classic American fare or indulging in treats, your tastebuds are sure to cry out for more. While on your way to your next Disney Cruise dining adventure, work up an appetite by taking the stairs!

C1oannD0po0.title: How to navigate your first day on a Disney cruise
C1oannD0po0.description:
Sailing on a Disney Cruise is an unforgettable experience. From pool parties to fine dining to Disney-style broadway shows, there’s never a dull moment on board. But with so many activities to choose from, how do you know where to start? Here are our tips for the first things you should do onboard a Disney Cruise. Plan your Disney cruise: http://bit.ly/1T5ovZ5

Step 1: B-line to lunch
Your stateroom won’t be ready until the early afternoon, so grab some lunch instead. Be sure to come hungry, because this is one of many bountiful meals included in your cruise price. 

Step 2: Download the Disney Cruise Line Navigator app
This app will help you keep your daily cruise plans on track. It includes information about the ship, daily activities and other helpful info. Search for ‘Disney Cruise Line’ in your app store and it will be downloaded in a flash!

Step 3: Take a quick tour of the ship
Get the lay of the land by taking a walk around the ship. You can reference the maps on the walls to get a good sense of where you are. This is the perfect opportunity to scope out all of the things you want to do during your cruise.  

Step 4: Make reservations for specialty dining and the spa
Every ship has fine dining restaurants and a luxurious spa. Although they are an extra cost, they are completely worth it! Spots fill up quickly and you won’t want to miss out.

Step 5: Sign the kids up for their clubs
Toddlers, kids, tweens and teens each have their own place to hang out. Get your kiddos signed up for the club in their age range. You’ll have a hard time peeling them away from all the fun.

Step 6: Ride the AquaDuck
Be one of the first people to experience this awesome water coaster. It zips you around the perimeter of the ship and gives you unobstructed views of the ocean. It’s a popular attraction, so check it off your list early!

Step 7: Kick back with a cocktail
There are plenty of places on deck to grab a cold drink. Stop by one of the bars and order your favorite concoction. You’ll be relaxing in no time!

Step 8: Sail away
After the muster drill, it’s time to sail away. Don’t miss the party on the pool deck! You can dance the afternoon away with all your Disney pals. It’s the perfect way to bid farewell to dry land. 

Step 9: Head back to your state room
Your luggage will be waiting for you in front of your stateroom. Open your room for the first time and sink in to your new home away from home. 

Step 10: Finish the evening with nighttime entertainment
Each night there is a new broadway-style show as well as plenty of activities. You can choose from dance clubs, trivia nights, movie screenings, wine tastings and so much more.

localized.title: How to navigate your first day on a Disney cruise
localized.description:
Sailing on a Disney Cruise is an unforgettable experience. From pool parties to fine dining to Disney-style broadway shows, there’s never a dull moment on board. But with so many activities to choose from, how do you know where to start? Here are our tips for the first things you should do onboard a Disney Cruise. Plan your Disney cruise: http://bit.ly/1T5ovZ5

Step 1: B-line to lunch
Your stateroom won’t be ready until the early afternoon, so grab some lunch instead. Be sure to come hungry, because this is one of many bountiful meals included in your cruise price. 

Step 2: Download the Disney Cruise Line Navigator app
This app will help you keep your daily cruise plans on track. It includes information about the ship, daily activities and other helpful info. Search for ‘Disney Cruise Line’ in your app store and it will be downloaded in a flash!

Step 3: Take a quick tour of the ship
Get the lay of the land by taking a walk around the ship. You can reference the maps on the walls to get a good sense of where you are. This is the perfect opportunity to scope out all of the things you want to do during your cruise.  

Step 4: Make reservations for specialty dining and the spa
Every ship has fine dining restaurants and a luxurious spa. Although they are an extra cost, they are completely worth it! Spots fill up quickly and you won’t want to miss out.

Step 5: Sign the kids up for their clubs
Toddlers, kids, tweens and teens each have their own place to hang out. Get your kiddos signed up for the club in their age range. You’ll have a hard time peeling them away from all the fun.

Step 6: Ride the AquaDuck
Be one of the first people to experience this awesome water coaster. It zips you around the perimeter of the ship and gives you unobstructed views of the ocean. It’s a popular attraction, so check it off your list early!

Step 7: Kick back with a cocktail
There are plenty of places on deck to grab a cold drink. Stop by one of the bars and order your favorite concoction. You’ll be relaxing in no time!

Step 8: Sail away
After the muster drill, it’s time to sail away. Don’t miss the party on the pool deck! You can dance the afternoon away with all your Disney pals. It’s the perfect way to bid farewell to dry land. 

Step 9: Head back to your state room
Your luggage will be waiting for you in front of your stateroom. Open your room for the first time and sink in to your new home away from home. 

Step 10: Finish the evening with nighttime entertainment

mXk5-2u0kw0.title: Sao Paulo Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
mXk5-2u0kw0.description:
Sao Paulo – Welcome to one of the world’s most populated cities. Check out the best spots to visit in Brazil’s exciting hub of business, culture, creativity and hospitality.

When ready, browse vacation packages to Sao Paulo: https://www.expedia.com/Sao-Paulo.d180023.Destination-Travel-Guides

Your #SaoPaulo #vacation should take you on a #tour of historic sites such as Pátio do Colégio and Praça da Sé which now houses the towering Metropolitan Cathedral. 

#Visit the city’s most esteemed museums: the São Paulo Museum of Art, on the famous Avenida Paulista, and the Pinacoteca do Estado. The Viaduto Santa Ifigenia, an art nouveau bridge, leads pedestrians to the ornate Municipal Theatre, with its impressive Sala São Paulo concert hall. Don’t miss Ibirapuera Park, which is home to the modern Ibirapuera Auditorium, the São Paulo Museum of Modern Art and the Afro Brazil Museum. Meet Brazil’s soccer heroes through the interactive exhibits of the Football Museum in Pacaembu Stadium. 

Explore all of São Paulo’s neighborhoods and bustling cultural hubs to discover that this city is not only the engine behind Brazil’s economy, but also its cultural powerhouse.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it.

YXz-erPr8B8.title: Montevideo Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
YXz-erPr8B8.description:
Montevideo – Uraguay’s capital welcomes visitors to its seaside city bounds. Explore Montevideo with us and start planning a trip here of your own. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Montevideo: https://www.expedia.com/Montevideo.d2461.Destination-Travel-Guides

Uruguay is emerging as one of South America’s favorite destinations. Its capital #Montevideo has a warm, temperate climate, pleasant sea breezes and miles of boulevards.

#Tour the city while on #vacation here and #visit the towers, squares and cathedrals of its Old Towns. Wander along the 19-mile long promenade, La Rambla leads to the city’s favorite playground: De Los Pocitos Beach.

Enjoy the proud local tradition of “parrilla". The best way to try it is to buy cuts of meat in the Mercado del Puerto, and have those cooked for you on the spot.

#Explore the UNESCO-listed Old Town of Colonia del Sacramento, with its landmark lighthouse, sleepy Plaza de Armas, historic Portón de Campo and atmospheric Street of Sighs.

Uruguay may be small, but its big heart and relaxing vibe creates a lifetime of memories.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Montevideo: https://www.expedia.com/Montevideo.dx2461

xjeegoHXTSg.title: Top 5 Favorite Things to Do at Walt Disney World
xjeegoHXTSg.description:
With seemingly endless things to do at Walt Disney World, how could anyone choose their favorite attraction? It was tough, but the Expedia Viewfinder travel blog team picked their 5 favorite things to do at Walt Disney World. Start planning your Disney vacation here: http://expd.us/IYaHIb
 
Here’s our countdown of the top 5 things to do at Walt Disney World.
 
“it’s a small world” (00:34) – Don’t miss this family-friendly classic. You’ll hop in a boat and sail through different cultures around the world.  
 
Expedition Everest (00:45) – If you love a good thrill, then check out this intense roller coaster at Disney’s Animal Kingdom. You’ll rush forwards and backwards through the Himalayas. 
 
World Showcase (01:05) – Travel around the globe in just one day at Epcot. You can stop by 11 countries and shop, eat and drink along the way. 
 
Tower of Terror (01:20) – Head straight for the Twilight Zone on this hair-raising ride. You’ll be taken through a spooky tale and dropped down an elevator shaft. 
 
Disney Springs (01:37) – Downtown Disney was officially renamed Disney Springs in September 2015. You can indulge in world-class shopping, amazing dining options and so many fun things to do. 
 
We’ll be posting more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort throughout 2016. Stay tuned for additional things to do and places to see. Want the latest updates? Search #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

waYWwTelGJA.title: What to Expect from Afternoon Tea in London | Expedia Viewfinder Travel Blog
waYWwTelGJA.description:
Kate Thomas from the Expedia Viewfinder travel blog shares what it's like to experience afternoon tea in London. She enjoyed a budget afternoon tea at Bea's of Bloomsbury. The cultural tradition began in the 1800s and it was a way for the upper class to stave off hunger pains between breakfast and dinner. Every afternoon tea is unique, but they all follow a general template. It includes three tiers of goodness. The first is full of savory sandwiches. The top two tiers have sweets like cupcakes, scones, lemon squares and raspberry marshmallows.

2nMDmCRcuEE.title: Top 5 Things to Do At Walt Disney World for Toddlers
2nMDmCRcuEE.description:
Walt Disney World is fun for children of all ages. Even the littlest ones have activities designed just for them. The Expedia Viewfinder travel blog team shares the top 5 Walt Disney World attractions for toddlers and younger kids. Start planning your Disney vacation here: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the top 5 things to do at Walt Disney World for toddlers.

Disney Junior Live on Stage (00:30) – Performed several times a day, this interactive show entertains preschoolers by giving them a chance to dance, sing and play along with all their Disney Junior pals.

“it’s a small world” (00:52) –  Set sail on this cultural voyage around the world. You’re guaranteed to be humming this catchy tune the rest of the day. 

Dumbo the Flying Elephant (01:18) – Fly high above Storybook Circus on this gentle ride at Magic Kingdom Park. Riders can adjust the height of their elephant for a more interactive experience. 

The Seas with Nemo & Friends (01:32) – Go on an underwater adventure to see Nemo. After climbing aboard a clam shell, they’re off for fun ride with the fun characters Disney Pixar’s Finding Nemo. 

Character Dining (01:48) –  No trip to Walt Disney World would be complete without dining with your favorite characters. Book your reservation in advance at Disneyworld.com. 

We’ll be posting more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort throughout 2016. Stay tuned for additional things to do and places to see. Want the latest updates? Search #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

zhtg9XgVwuM.title: Edinburgh Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
zhtg9XgVwuM.description:
Edinburgh – The capital of Scotland and safely proclaimed to be one of the world’s most beautiful cities. Click play to check out the top sights. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Edinburgh: https://www.expedia.com/Edinburgh.d6069845.Destination-Travel-Guides

A #vacation to #Edinburgh lets you rub shoulders with history. Its Old Town and Royal Mile are filled with the ghosts of medieval merchants and poets, while its New Town shines with the glories of the Scottish Enlightenment.  

To see Edinburgh in all her glory, climb to Arthur’s Seat, the highest of the city’s seven peaks. #Visit Edinburgh Castle, the symbol of Scotland. Over the last eleven centuries, this castle has been laid siege to 26 times but still it stands, a testimony to the indomitable spirit of the Scots.
 
Explore centuries of innovation at the Scottish Museum, or head to South Queensferry to see the Forth Bridge, an engineering marvel when it opened in 1890. The Royal Botanic Gardens is one of the world’s oldest and most important centers of botanical science, yet it’s still a place which invites one to slow down.
 
For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Edinburgh: https://www.expedia.com/Edinburgh.dx6069845

Subscribe to Expedia’s YouTube Channel for great travel videos and join the conversation on the best vacation ideas.

eFTEsM5vhjM.title: Top 5 Walt Disney World Hacks
eFTEsM5vhjM.description:
Vacations can be tricky to plan, but your next trip to Walt Disney World doesn’t have to be! These 5 Walt Disney World hacks will make the process much easier. The Expedia Viewfinder travel blog team uncovers their top vacation hacks. Start planning your Disney vacation here: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the top 5 Walt Disney World Hacks.

Stay at a Disney Resort Hotel (00:35) – You’ll save time by staying closer to the magic and you’ll have free transportation to get you there. Hotels range from value to deluxe. 

Extra Magic Hours (00:54) –  This perk allows you to arrive at the parks earlier than the regular posted hours. You even get to stay later in the evenings. This extra time gives you a chance to knock out even more of your must-do list. 

Walt Disney World Vacation Package Deals (01:29) – Save money on your trip by booking your flight, hotel and park tickets together on Expedia.com. 

Water Parks Fun & More Option (01:43) – Enjoy golfing, splash around at the water parks and make the most of your trip with this add-on. 

Fastpass+ (02:02) –  Reserve time for your favorite Disney attractions online up to 60 days in advance. Use the My Disney Experience website or mobile app. You can also change your plans on the go. Less time waiting in line means more time for ice cream!

We’ll be posting more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort throughout 2016. Stay tuned for additional things to do and places to see. Want the latest updates? Search #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

eriZg52f-pQ.title: Cocktail Recipes Around the World | Expedia Viewfinder Travel Blog
eriZg52f-pQ.description:
Captain and Clark from the Expedia Viewfinder travel blog share their favorite cocktail recipes from around the world.

Brazilian Fire - This drink is made with cachaça, the most popular distilled alcohol beverage in Brazil. Soak a habanero pepper in a bottle of cachaça for two weeks. Then pour 2 oz of the cachaça into 1 oz of lemon juice, 1 oz of lime juice and 1 oz of Grand Marnier. Serve over ice and enjoy!

Costa Brava Sangria - Take a traditional sangria recipe and substitute the red wine for Cava, the Spanish sparkling wine. 

Odin's Revenge - Mix 2 oz of Brennivin into a glass of porter, add a dash of bitters and drizzle with maple syrup. 

Sri Lankan River Boat - The base of this drink is Ceylon, liquor made from the distilled sap of coconut blossom. Stir 2 oz of Ceylon into a ginger beer, add a little bit of gin and a squeeze of lime. 

Pele's Passion - Combine 3 oz of Koloa Spiced Rum with 2 oz of guava juice, 1 tablespoon of passion fruit butter and half of a mango. Blend it all together and serve over ice for a liquid paradise.

Soju Cocktail - Pour soju, a Korean liquor, into a pitcher of ice and blend with kiwi and strawberry. 

Check out more travel fun on our blog: http://viewfinder.expedia.com

0g0BSgvKF2o.title: Top 5 Hidden Things in Walt Disney World
0g0BSgvKF2o.description:
With so much to see and do at Walt Disney World, it can be easy to miss some of the magic that’s hidden in plain sight. The Expedia Viewfinder travel blog team went on a mission to find the top hidden things in Walt Disney World. Start planning your Disney vacation here: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the top 5 hidden things in Walt Disney World.

Shop Windows (00:30) – At Magic Kingdom park, you can see the artfully decorated windows high above the shops along Main Street, U.S.A. The names written on the windows are a who’s who of Disney legends, including Walt Disney himself.

Forced Perspective (00:45) –  When strolling down Main Street U.S.A, make sure to look up. You’ll notice that the upper floors of the buildings get progressively shorter. This is effect gives the illusion of height without obstructing your view of Cinderella Castle. 

Hidden Mickey (01:17) – Think you spy the iconic Mickey shape in unlikely locales throughout the theme parks and resorts? You might be right. Look around and you might spot some Hidden Mickeys in unusual places.

Sorcerers of the Magic Kingdom (01:36) – Pick up special cards and you’re off on an adventure to pinning good against evil with hidden clues throughout the park. 

Tree of Life (01:55) – Go to Disney’s Animal Kingdom to find the Tree of Life. Disney Imagineers went to great lengths to blend more than 300 amazing animal shapes into the branches and trunk of the park’s towering icon.

We’ll be posting more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort throughout 2016. Stay tuned for additional things to do and places to see. Want the latest updates? Search #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

With winter in full swing the city was at its most festive. Here is my guide to a mother-daughter winter getaway in New York City! 

Get an Expedia Viewfinder look into New York things to do. Follow Courtney Scott as she adventures with her mom through the Big Apple, uncovering the best activities and experiences along the way. KWY4z4NFkkI.title: Cook Islands Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
KWY4z4NFkkI.description:
The Cook Islands – The land of pristine white sands fringed by coconut palms. Experience the castaway island magic as you follow our journey through paradise.

When ready, browse vacation packages to the Cook Islands: https://www.expedia.com/Cook-Islands.d41.Destination-Travel-Guides

Situated at the very centre of Polynesia, a mere four-hour flight from New Zealand, the #CookIslands is an archipelago nation comprised of 15 islands. It is spread across an area in the South Pacific three times the size of Texas.

According to legend, these tiny islands, dotted amongst the vast ocean, were discovered thousands of years ago by the very finest Polynesian seafarers. Guided by the stars and using other sophisticated navigation techniques, they landed their legendary double hulled Vakas and set about creating paradise.

It has been almost 250 years since Captain Cook became the first European to discover these islands and yet there is a gentle timelessness that endures here. #Vacation here and discover the generous rhythm and warm hospitality of the Cook Islands for yourself.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around the Cook Islands: https://www.expedia.com/Cook-Islands.dx41

EL0-OIyeMsA.title: Top 5 Walt Disney World Thrill Rides
EL0-OIyeMsA.description:
Walt Disney World Resort is packed with roller coasters and waterslides that are sure to make you scream. From Animal Kingdom to Magic Kingdom Park, don’t miss these high-intensity thrill rides at Walt Disney World Resort. Start planning your vacation: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the Top 5 Walt Disney World thrill rides for the ultimate experience.

Summit Plummet (00:27) – Slide down one of the tallest and fastest free-fall body slides in the world at Disney’s Blizzard Beach. It’s 120 feet high and riders reach speeds of 55 mph! 

Splash Mountain (00:51) – Head to Frontierland at Magic Kingdom Park to experience this iconic log flume ride. You’re guaranteed to get wet, which makes it the perfect way to cool off on a hot day. 

Big Thunder Mountain (01:21) – The old west has never been more exciting. This fast-paced ride races through an abandoned mine. Hold on tight!

Space Mountain (01:40) – No Disney vacation would be complete without a ride on Space Mountain. Towering over Tomorrowland, this futuristic, indoor, in-the-dark roller coaster has been thrilling Disney guests for more than four decades.

Expedition Everest (02:00) – Go to Disney’s Animal Kindgom to find the newest thrill ride. Expedition Everest takes you on hair-raising journey through the Himalayas – forwards and backwards! Watch out for the yeti. 

We’ll bringing sharing more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort throughout 2016. Stay tuned for more things to do and places to see. Want the latest updates? Search #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

UdJJLpx169M.title: Sunshine Coast Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
UdJJLpx169M.description:
Sunshine Coast – A region blessed by mother nature, venture here to enjoy miles of spectacular coastline on one side and tranquil hinterland on the other.

When ready, browse vacation packages to Sunshine Coast: https://www.expedia.com/Sunshine-Coast.d180069.Destination-Travel-Guides

Just over an hour north of Queensland’s capital, Brisbane, lies Australia’s #SunshineCoast. Endless golden beaches, year-round swimming and an easygoing attitude, make this the perfect #vacation spot to slow down and unwind. In this beautiful region, the casual glamour of Noosa, merges into the family fun of Caloundra and blends with the artistic flair of the hinterland.

The most famous town is Noosa Heads - an indulgent and stylish getaway with white beaches almost completely surrounded by national park. Follow winding tracks to unspoilt headlands then cool off in crystal clear waters. 

#Explore rock pools at Mooloolaba Beach or learn more about the ocean at Sea Life - Underwater World. Wildlife experiences don’t come much more intense than the legendary Crocodile Hunter’s Australia Zoo.

Follow sandy footprints along the Sunshine Coast and leave a few of your own in this beautiful place.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Sunshine Coast: https://www.expedia.com/Sunshine-Coast.dx180069

9EDhdoSSdFk.title: Top 5 Walt Disney World Special Moments
9EDhdoSSdFk.description:
Walt Disney World Resort is the perfect place to celebrate magical moments and special occasions. Whether it’s your anniversary or birthday, you won’t regret spending your next milestone at “The Most Magical Place on Earth.” Begin planning your vacation: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the Top 5 ways to enjoy a special moment at Walt Disney World Resort.

Go on a Carriage Ride (00:35) – At Disney’s Fort Wilderness Resort and Campground, you can take a private carriage ride through a magical forest. You just might spot some wildlife and critters along the way too.

Dine at the California Grill (00:44) – Enjoy fine dining at the California Grill on the 15th floor of Disney’s Contemporary Resort. The restaurant has sweeping views of Magic Kingdom Park. It’s also prime seating for viewing the fireworks show! 

Stage a Marriage Proposal (01:00) – Cinderella Castle is a romantic backdrop for lovers. If you’re ready to pop the question to your sweetheart, then you can arrange your own Disney-style marriage proposal. 

Take a Tandem Parasail Ride (01:22) – Nothing brings a couple closer together than a little adventure. Fly high in the sky on a tandem parasail. You’ll to a bird’s eye view of nearby parks and resorts. 

Private Fireworks Cruise (01:33) – Watch the fireworks from the best seat in the resort. Reserve a private cruise and float on the lake during the show. You’ll never forget the way the lights sparkle off the water.

Stay tuned for more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort. We’ll be sharing additional things to do and places to see all throughout 2016. Can’t wait for more? Check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

5s1Ntz11P2g.title: Top 5 Sweet Treats and Desserts At Walt Disney World Resort
5s1Ntz11P2g.description:
Walt Disney World Resort is home to many unique desserts. You can easily taste your way through the parks at various restaurants, bakeries, and snack carts. Start planning your trip: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the Top 5 sweet treats and desserts at Walt Disney World Resort.

Tonga Toast (00:25) – Kona Café at Disney’s Polynesian Village Resort serves this all-time breakfast favorite. The dish is sourdough bread, dipped in batter, rolled in cinnamon sugar and stuffed with bananas. Top it off with strawberry syrup for extra sweetness! 

Mickey Waffle (00:41) – You can’t go to WDW without trying the waffles. This classic treat can be found at most breakfast places around the parks. Served with maple syrup and your choice of bacon or sausage. 

Caramel Apples (00:54) – Don’t miss these themed treats at the Main Street Confectionary in Magic Kingdom Park. They are made in many shapes and designs, including Mickey, Minnie and special holiday themes. 

Le Fou’s Brew (01:14) – Named after Le Fou from Beauty and the Beast, this cold drink is suitable for all ages. It’s a blend of frozen apple juice, toasted marshmallows and topped with passion fruit mango foam. 

Dole Whip (01:42) – This is the most popular sweet treat. Found at Adventureland in Magic Kingdom Park, this tasty frozen dessert is a pineapple dream. It doesn’t get any sweeter than this. 

Stay tuned for more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort. We’ll be sharing additional things to do and places to see all throughout 2016. Can’t wait for more? Check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

jPX6SKSq3rg.title: Trujillo Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
jPX6SKSq3rg.description:
Trujillo – Known as the Peruvian Capital of Culture, this Spanish colonial city in the northern desert of Peru is a vibrant place, with colorful architecture and proud Latino traditions. 


When ready, browse vacation packages to Trujillo: https://www.expedia.com/Trujillo.d3537.Destination-Travel-Guides

A #Trujillo #vacation will invite you to #explore the ancient ruins of lost civilizations which dot the surrounding desert coast. Some 2,000 years ago, the Moche people and later the Chimú, managed to cultivate the arid Moche Valley and build thriving cities such as Chan Chan, made entirely from adobe bricks. 

These pre-Columbian civilizations also created the mighty Temple of the Sun and the Temple of the Moon, wove reed fishing boats and dug canals for irrigation. 
The museum in the coastal site of El Brujo contains a tattooed mummy of a warrior leader or priestess, who was dubbed the Lady of Cao. Find out more about these ancient cultures in Trujillo’s Archaeological Museum. Then, admire the region’s pure-bred Paso Horses during a Marinera show with costumed dancers. End your stay with a visit to the Cathedral and Freedom Monument on Plaza de Armas in the city’s picturesque Historic Centre.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Trujillo: https://www.expedia.com/Trujillo.dx3537

Some 2,000 years ago, the Moche people and later the Chimú, managed to cultivate the arid Moche Valley and build thriving cities such as Chan Chan, made entirely from adobe bricks. 

These pre-Columbian civilizations also created the mighty Temple of the Sun and the Temple of the Moon, wove reed fishing boats and dug canals for irrigation. 
The museum in the coastal site of El Brujo contains a tattooed mummy of a warrior leader or priestess, who was dubbed the Lady of Cao. Find out more about these ancient cultures in Trujillo’s Archaeological Museum. Then, admire the region’s pure-bred Paso Horses during a Marinera show with costumed dancers. End your stay with a visit to the Cathedral and Freedom Monument on Plaza de Armas in the city’s picturesque Historic Centre.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Trujillo: https://www.expedia.com/Trujillo.dx3537

4pa0tUl6RGI.title: Top 5 Things To Do At Walt Disney World Resort For Adults
4pa0tUl6RGI.description:
Walt Disney World Resort isn’t just for kids. There are plenty of adult activities for some grown up fun. Start planning your trip: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the Top 5 things to do for adults at Walt Disney World Resort.

Epcot International Food & Wine Festival (00:27) – Indulge with food, wine, beer and spirits from around the globe at this annual event. The festival takes place every fall at Epcot Theme Park. Don’t forget to stop by the music stage for concerts throughout the day!

Disney Springs (00:48) – Downtown Disney has completely transformed – with a new name too! With world-class shopping, dining and entertainment, you could spend days exploring and enjoying the dozens of new sights.

Behind-the-Scenes Tours (01:08) – The Backstage Magic Tour takes you to all sorts of insider spots like the Walt Disney World Nursery. See the famous topiaries being pruned and shaped to your favorite Disney characters.

Trader Sam's Grog Grotto and Tiki Bar (01:45) – Head to Disney’s Polynesian Village Resort to sip on tropical drinks and enjoy the island music and ambiance. You might even get a little show when you least expect it! 

Fine Dining (02:16) – Walt Disney World Resort has a bevy of signature restaurants to discover. Stop by the California Grill at the Contemporary Resort for exquisite dishes and unbeatable views of Magic Kingdom Park. Hint: It’s one of the best spots to watch the fireworks show!

Stay tuned for more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort. We’ll be sharing additional things to do and places to see all throughout 2016. Can’t wait for more? Check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

suNZvrochDM.title: Top 5 New Attractions at Walt Disney World Resort
suNZvrochDM.description:
Even after nearly 45 years, the Walt Disney World Resort remains as fresh and exciting as ever. Start planning your trip: http://expd.us/IYaHIb

Here’s our countdown of the Top 5 Walt Disney World Resort attractions that are new.

Seven Dwarfs Mine Train (00:35) – This new roller coaster in Magic Kingdom Park takes you on a wild ride through a diamond mine. Fans of Snow White will love spotting familiar faces and singing to “Heigh Ho” all along the way. Don’t forget to smile for the cameras!

Lots of Frozen (00:50) – Love Frozen? You’re in luck. You can watch Elsa and Ana at the Festival of Fantasy Parade or meet them at Princess Fairytale Hall for a photo opp. There’s even a Frozen sing-a-long show at Disney’s Hollywood Studios.

Harambe Market (01:09) – Take a break from the rides and enjoy authentic African street food at this market in Disney’s Animal Kingdom. The new eatery serves ribs, skewers, kabobs and other regional flavors that will make you want to come back for seconds. 

Disney’s Polynesian Villas and Bungalows (01:28) – These new overwater bungalows look and feel like Bora Bora, but have a beautiful view of Magic Kingdom Park. Guests can enjoy multiple bedrooms, luxury amenities and even a private plunge pool. Hint: It’s the ultimate view for the fireworks show.

Disney Springs (01:51) – Downtown Disney has completely transformed – with a new name too! Dozens of new shops and restaurants have been added to enhance the shopping, dining and entertainment experience. Visit a new bar that’s themed after Indiana Jones, dine at a Japanese restaurant run by the celebrity chef Masaharu Morimoto or order a massive Baked Alaska at The Boathouse. You can also take a ride in a vintage amphicar that drives right into the lake.

Stay tuned for more Top 5 videos about Walt Disney World Resort attractions. We’ll be sharing additional things to do and places to see all throughout 2016. Can’t wait for more? Check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media to get the latest news.

MlrzLYqIsE8.title: Lima Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
MlrzLYqIsE8.description:
Lima – Welcome to the capital of Peru, where city sights are as diverse as the nation’s landscapes. Follow us through this South American city and take note of the top spots to visit. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Lima: https://www.expedia.com/Lima.d178277.Destination-Travel-Guides

#Lima gives access to the mystical city of Machu Picchu in the Andes, Lake Titicaca in the highlands, the lush Amazon jungle and Peru’s coastal desert. But, before you go to see all of this, it’s worth exploring the capital first.

In Lima’s Historic Center is the Plaza de Armas, also known as the Plaza Mayor. #Visit Government Palace which is still the official seat of government today.

Continue your #vacation outside of the city center. The Bajada de los Baños in bohemian Barranco is home to the Bridge of Sighs. In Miraflores is Huaca Pucllana, a pre-Columbian temple of some 1,500 years old. The Museo Larco in Pueblo Libre contains amazing pre-Columbian artifacts. 

Don’t miss Lima’s parks. Parque de las Leyendas is a zoo and Parque de Exposición has fountains to play in and an awe-inspiring light show.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Lima: https://www.expedia.com/Lima.dx178277

GUMXv0VEtoc.title: Mexico City Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
GUMXv0VEtoc.description:
Mexico City – One of the financial powerhouses and cultural capitals of Latin America. Explore the colorful city here and start planning an adventure of your own!

Check out all the places we visited in this video: https://viewfinder.expedia.com/mexico-city-vacation-ideas-planning-itinerary-travel-video/

When ready, browse vacation packages to Mexico City: https://www.expedia.com/Mexico-City.d178285.Destination-Travel-Guides

 #MexicoCity welcomes visitors to its warm cultural heart. A #vacation here should feature the Centro Histórico district, where 1500 heritage buildings vie for your attention, including museums and galleries.
 
Head to Chapultepec Park, one of the largest urban parks in the world. Pay your respects to the Niños Heroes, a monument which honors the six boy soldiers who gave their lives defending Castillo de Chapultepec. Today, the castle serves as the National Museum of History. At Xochimilco, simply float away on a riot of color on the last of the city’s Aztec canals.
 
In the early 20th century the district’s artists, writers and intellectuals inspired not only Mexico, but the entire world. #Visit The Blue House, the birthplace of Frieda Kahlo, and the Museo Casa Estudio Diego Rivera y Frida Kahlo, where these two giants of Mexican art worked, lived and loved.  

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Mexico City: https://www.expedia.com/Mexico-City.dx178285

Oex1-NHC_h4.title: Top 5 Walt Disney World Resorts
Oex1-NHC_h4.description:
There are more than 25 themed Walt Disney World resorts. How could you possibly choose one? The Expedia Viewfinder blog team shares the Top 5 resorts at Walt Disney World. Start planning your trip: http://expd.us/IYaHIb 

Disney’s Art of Animation Resort (00:31) – This is a family favorite. The rooms are designed after The Little Mermaid, Finding Nemo, The Lion King and Cars. Larger suites allow the whole family to spread out. Check it out: http://bit.ly/1RN6Tjt 

Disney’s Polynesian Village Resort (00:49) – Guests are transported to a tropical paradise. The brand new over-water bungalows have multiple bedrooms, private plunge pools and stellar views of Magic Kingdom Park. Reserve your room: http://bit.ly/1PbTFYz 

Disney’s Animal Kingdom Lodge (01:08) – This African-themed resort is surrounded by more than 45 acres of savanna – complete with animals! Look outside your window to see giraffes, zebras and more African wildlife. Book your stay: http://bit.ly/1UPygZo 

Disney’s Port Orleans Resort-Riverside (01:24) – Experience rural Louisiana and southern hospitality at this riverside resort. The royal-themed rooms are fit for a queen. Guests can stroll along the water or go for a bike ride. Plan your trip: http://bit.ly/1ZuOtdj 

Disney’s Grand Floridian Resort and Spa (01:51) – This Victorian-style resort boasts unparalleled luxury amenities. You’ll feel like royalty when you walk into the immaculate lobby with cascading chandeliers and towering flower arrangements. See the rooms: http://bit.ly/1P1r8La 

Stay tuned for more videos! The Expedia Viewfinder blog team visited Orlando to discover the best Walt Disney World Resorts. Throughout 2016, we’ll be sharing more top things to do and places to stay. Check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media for more Disney fun.

IEPYQ_PX_Ug.description:
At Expedia, we want to help you get the most out of your vacation. Whether you're touring the historic Alcatraz prison or riding a Segway through Golden Gate Park, Expedia offers the best things to do, including activities, attractions, tours, and shows, in San Francisco. Visit http://expedia.com and click on Things to Do—because getting there is only the first step!

Click on each activity in the video to book your own experience, such as walking tours and seaplane rides, or just go there directly:

• Alcatraz Package: Hop-On Hop-Off Cruise & City Tour: https://www.expedia.com/things-to-do/alcatraz-package-hop-on-hop-off-cruise-city-tour-by-big-bus.a192704.activity-details?srp=true&location=San%20Francisco%20(and%20vicinity),%20California,%20United%20States%20of%20America

16Y15eImbmY.title: Top 5 Holiday Celebrations at Walt Disney World Resort
16Y15eImbmY.description:
Walt Disney World Resort is the perfect place to spend Christmas, Thanksgiving, Halloween, Fourth of July, or simply springtime. Plan your vacation here: http://expd.us/IYaHIb
 
Here’s some of the top things to do at Walt Disney World Resort throughout the seasons.
 
Springtime (00:54) –Epcot is in full bloom from March through May during the Epcot International Flower and Garden Festival. Visitors can watch gardening demos, eat fresh seasonal foods, dance at daily concerts and view thousands of flowers and more than 100 of topiaries.
 
Fourth of July (01:19) – Walt Disney World Resort is famous for their fireworks shows. Watch the resort light up with a special 4th of July fireworks display – “Celebrate America - A Fourth of July Concert in the Sky”. For more patriotic fun, get a history lesson at the American Adventure at Epcot and see all of the US presidents at the Hall of Presidents at Magic Kingdom Park.
 
Halloween (01:55)– Magic Kingdom Park gets a full Halloween makeover with scarecrows and pumpkins during September and October. Dress-up, trick-or-treat and watch a special parade and fireworks show during Mickey’s Not-So-Scary Halloween Party.
 
Thanksgiving (02:27)– You don’t have to miss out on a classic turkey dinner if you’re celebrating Thanksgiving during a Walt Disney World vacation. Restaurants throughout the park serve full turkey dinners. No matter what time of the year it is, turkey legs can always be found at food carts.
 
Christmas (03:01) – Walt Disney World Christmas is one of the most magical times of the year. The parks get decked out for Christmas. Visitors can meet Santa and watch Queen Elsa transform Cinderella Castle into a nightly ice show at Magic Kingdom Park. Shop for unique gifts and learn about holiday traditions from around the globe at Epcot too.
 
Stay tuned for more videos! The Expedia Viewfinder blog team visited Orlando to discover the best of Walt Disney World Resort. Throughout 2016, we’ll be sharing the top things to do and places to stay. Check out #ExpediaAtDisney on social media for more Disney fun.

vzSHcyXfNPw.title: Iceland Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
vzSHcyXfNPw.description:
Iceland – a nation windswept and beautiful from mountain to sea. Check out our footage to discover the natural and manmade marvels of the island. 

Check out all the places we visited in this video: https://viewfinder.expedia.com/iceland-vacation-ideas-planning-itinerary-travel-video/

When ready, browse vacation packages to Iceland: https://www.expedia.com/Iceland.d79.Destination-Travel-Guides

With a population of just under 350,000, #Iceland can feel like the most isolated place on earth. Yet with its capital Reykjavik, being only a three-hour flight from London and just under six from New York, it’s a #vacation spot that’s in easy reach.
 
Reykjavik is relaxed and welcoming yet possesses a cultural life that holds its own against other European capitals. 

Many of the country’s most popular #sights are within easy reach of Reykjavík. Iceland’s main ring road strings together an endless series of epic landscapes. 

#Explore Iceland, where every side road is a story waiting to unfold. So, come and live your own Icelandic story. It’s one you’ll keep telling for the rest of your days.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Iceland: https://www.expedia.com/Iceland.dx79

nD_dFyfOXIo.title: Patagonia Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
nD_dFyfOXIo.description:
Patagonia – travel here to the land that time forgot and set out on the journey of a lifetime where Mother Nature runs the show. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Patagonia: https://www.expedia.com/Chilean-Patagonia.d6053659.Destination-Travel-Guides

#Patagonia, the fabled ‘edge of the world’, spans the southernmost regions of Chile and Argentina and can be rugged and desolate as well as breathtakingly beautiful and inviting.

This last frontier of South America is a colorful mosaic of snow-capped mountains, icebergs, volcanoes, glaciers, forests, lakes and vast steppe plains. This is a land of legendary beauty.

On the Argentinean side, the scenic Road of the 7 Lakes takes you from San Martín de los Andes to Villa La Angostura and finally San Carlos de Bariloche, a popular ski resort on the shores of Lake Nahuel Huapi. Trekking opportunities, national parks and awe-inspiring glaciers await you when on #vacation here. 

On the Chilean side of Patagonia, the regional capital Punta Arenas attracts visitors with its colonial architecture, cultural attractions and hospitality. Caves, horse riding and hiking opportunities, peaks and waterfalls are ripe for exploring. 

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Patagonia: https://www.expedia.com/Chilean-Patagonia.dx6053659

On the Argentinean side, the scenic Road of the 7 Lakes takes you from San Martín de los Andes to Villa La Angostura and finally San Carlos de Bariloche, a popular ski resort on the shores of Lake Nahuel Huapi. Trekking opportunities, national parks and awe-inspiring glaciers await you when on #vacation here. 

On the Chilean side of Patagonia, the regional capital Punta Arenas attracts visitors with its colonial architecture, cultural attractions and hospitality. Caves, horse riding and hiking opportunities, peaks and waterfalls are ripe for exploring. 

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Patagonia: https://www.expedia.com/Chilean-Patagonia.dx6053659

KLvDb3L1b60.title: San Marino Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
KLvDb3L1b60.description:
San Marino – With an area of just over 20 square miles, join us as we explore Europe’s third smallest country. Make no mistake, there’s no shortage of cool spots to check out.

When ready, browse vacation packages to San Marino: https://www.expedia.com/San-Marino.d6054756.Destination-Travel-Guides

Find the longstanding city-state, #SanMarino, in eastern Italy’s countryside. A #vacation here means enjoying age-old architecture, excellent food, and shopping delights. 

Rising from the republic’s rolling hills is Mount Titano, where the country’s founder, Saint Marinus, sought refuge in the 3rd Century. Over the centuries, three towers were built to ward off invaders; today these towers watch over a country overflowing with history, culture and beauty.

Just beyond the towers lies the republic’s ancient capital, San Marino City. The heart and soul of this city is Liberty Square, home to the Statue of Liberty and the Palazzo Pubblico. Wherever you turn you’ll see tributes to the republic’s founder, no more so than in San Marino Basilica, where the bones of the saint now rest beneath the altar. 

San Marino is a welcoming escape for lovers of art and history, and a tax-free haven for shoppers. 

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it.

5kBQ4c_xw-o.title: Santiago Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
5kBQ4c_xw-o.description:
Santiago de Chile – A city of extremes. Explore the cosmopolitan South American capital for the perfect mix of both historic and ultra-modern attractions.

When ready, browse vacation packages to Santiago: https://www.expedia.com/Santiago.d178306.Destination-Travel-Guides

#Santiago de Chile is surrounded by the world’s longest mountain range, driest desert, largest ocean and southernmost grassy plains. Enjoy the patchwork of natural treasures with a #vacation here. 

The lively Plaza de Armas houses the divine Metropolitan Cathedral and the National History Museum. Santa Lucía Hill is the place where the city was founded by the Spanish in the 16th-century and the Chilean Museum of pre-Colombian Art shows what life was like here before colonial rule.

La Moneda Palace is the seat of government and the place of Augusto Pinochet’s 1973 military coup. The Museum of Memory and Human Rights documents the dictator’s repressive regime.

Santiago has many city parks to explore, such as: Parque Bicentenario, Parque de las Esculturas and Parque Forestal.

On your #visit here, find colorful street art, craft shops and sidewalk cafés in Bellavista. 

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Santiago: https://www.expedia.com/Santiago.dx178306

o_TKIM1vUEs.title: Manchester Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
o_TKIM1vUEs.description:
Manchester – A city whose history speaks to brave innovation. Check out the top spots in the city to explore and the cultural and historical sights to enjoy. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Manchester: https://www.expedia.com/Manchester.d180010.Destination-Travel-Guides

#Manchester is a city of firsts. #Vacation here to what was the epicenter of the Industrial Revolution, the place where mankind first split the atom, and the birthplace of the modern computer.
 
In Castlefield, #visit the remains of a Roman fort, Bridgewater Canal, and some of the mills which once generated incredible wealth for the city. 
 
The Town Hall was built to rival the great buildings of London. Many of the treasures sourced by merchants during the Industrial Revolution now reside in the Manchester Art Gallery and the Manchester Museum.
 
The People’s History Museum celebrates those who challenged Britain’s rigid political and class systems. At the world’s oldest surviving railway station, you’ll find The Museum of Science and Industry, while the Imperial War Museum North reminds us of the human cost of warfare.
 
Learn about the city’s footballing history at the National Football Museum, or see a match at Old Trafford.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Manchester: https://www.expedia.com/Manchester.dx2205

4QJ4ALxD978.title: Fuerteventura Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
4QJ4ALxD978.description:
Fuerteventura – The second largest of the Canary Islands, a Spanish archipelago situated in the Atlantic Ocean. This island is famous for stunning beaches, picturesque villages and year-round sunshine.

When ready, browse vacation packages to Fuerteventura: https://www.expedia.com/Fuerteventura.d1263.Destination-Travel-Guides

While on #vacation to #Fuerteventura visit Corralejo, one of the island’s largest resort towns and the perfect place from which to explore the Corralejo Dunes National Park. #Visit Morro Jable, a town famed for seafood restaurants and a picturesque lighthouse. Gorgeous beaches run the length of the Jandia Peninsula, reaching all the way to Costa Calma. 

Head inland to explore the island’s amazing volcanic landscapes and villages. Fuerteventura is also home to many romantic buildings and churches such as the parish church at La Oliva and the town hall in Pajara. Cotillo is perhaps the most picturesque village on the entire island. Stroll the old harbour and admire the original windmills. 

In an archipelago acclaimed for beaches, Fuerteventura has been blessed with some of the biggest and most beautiful. Combined with its perfect weather and incredible landscapes, this is the perfect island to relax, recharge and reconnect with nature.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Fuerteventura: https://www.expedia.com/Fuerteventura.dx1263

Sj-VzFlJ14o.title: Canberra Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
Sj-VzFlJ14o.description:
Canberra – Purpose built as Australia’s capital city, Canberra is a 3-hour drive from both the snowy mountains and the beautiful beaches of New South Wales. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Canberra: https://www.expedia.com/Canberra.d6049663.Destination-Travel-Guides

Canberra is a city which honors Australia’s past and shapes its future, yet #Canberra is far more than a political capital. 

At the heart of Canberra’s creation story is Lake Burley Griffin. In 1911, the government launched an international design competition seeking a master plan for a brand new city. The victor, Chicago architect Walter Burley Griffin, won with a garden city design focused on a man-made lake which fits perfectly within the landscape. When, the nation’s Governor General stood in a dusty paddock in 1913 and announced the name of the new capital, he told the nation that the city had, lying before it, a splendid destiny. 

Over 100 years later, that destiny has been fulfilled in a city that preserves the great chapters of Australia’s history and continues on to the next. #Vacation here to become a part of it, and keep the memories of your #visit for your own story. 

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it. 

More travel information around Canberra: https://www.expedia.com/Canberra.dx6049663

ka-ZgwCXKho.title: Venice Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
ka-ZgwCXKho.description:
The Italian city of Venice is a city like no other, rising from the waters of Venice Lagoon. Follow us through the historic streets – and canals – and see why Venice should be firmly on your bucket list!

When ready, browse vacation packages to Venice: https://www.expedia.com/Venice.d179981.Destination-Travel-Guides

Begin your #Venice #vacation in the central district of San Marco. Journey along one of the world’s great aquatic thoroughfares, The Grand Canal. Glide past elegant palazzos; today many of these palaces house important museums and galleries. 
 
Known as The City Of Bridges, Venice has hundreds to discover. The Accademia Bridge offers some of the Grand Canal’s finest views. The oldest of the Grand Canal’s four crossings is the Rialto Bridge, which serves as the gateway to the Rialto Markets. The most famous of all is the Bridge of Sighs, which connects Doge’s Palace to the historic prison.
 
Venice is a city to get lost in, so put away your map and let her surprise you. Just remember, this city smiles upon those who linger. So stay for a few nights, or #explore for a month, and savor every moment she has to offer.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it.

35Z4GGvCmlU.title: Ho Chi Minh City Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
35Z4GGvCmlU.description:
Ho Chi Minh City – Visit the southern tip of Vietnam for one of South East Asia’s emerging boom cities. Check out the best things to see and do in the city!

When ready, browse vacation packages to Ho Chi Minh City: https://www.expedia.com/Ho-Chi-Minh-City.d178262.Destination-Travel-Guides

#HoChiMinhCity is Vietnam’s largest city and its economic engine room. The city has an irrepressible soul and an entrepreneurial energy that hums day and night. Despite almost a century of colonialism and conflict, today this city is renowned for its warm hospitality. 

In Ho Chi Minh City, boulevards built during the French colonial era are lined with cutting edge skyscrapers, while jasmine scented temples gently rub shoulders with chic rooftop bars

More than 9 million people call Ho Chi Minh City home and the energy of its streets is part of its charm. Join the buzz with a #vacation here. The city is divided into a series of numbered districts. District One is where almost all of the city’s main #attractions can be found.

Dynamic, chaotic and energizing – there is no better #destination to plug into the pulse of 21st century #Asia.

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it.

N9q9uNa4DAg.title: One Day in Budapest | Expedia
N9q9uNa4DAg.description:
If you’ve landed a long layover in Budapest, Hungary, start planning your itinerary. After all, there’s no need to waste the day in the airport terminal when you could be venturing around the nation’s capital. The clock is ticking until your next flight, but there’s lots you can do in just 24 hours in Budapest. 

When you’re looking to experience Budapest in a day, start your adventures at the Royal Palace on Castle Hill. The compound was built in the 13th century, and it includes popular attractions such as the Hungarian National Gallery and the Budapest History Museum. Next, check out the massive Hungarian Parliament Building and gaze at the Holy Crown of Hungary, located in the central hall. If you still have time to spare during your layover, take a dip in the steamy water at the Szechenyi Medicinal Bath, stroll around the Liberty Statue on Gellert Hill, and make a stop at world-famous St. Stephen’s Basilica. 

Even if you’re limited to one day in Budapest, you’ll have the opportunity to see some of the city’s most valued sites. Whether you venture to the historic spots or simply mosey across the Chain Bridge, you just may find yourself hoping for a flight cancellation.

JHWlSrIgwwE.title: Lanzarote Vacation Travel Guide | Expedia
JHWlSrIgwwE.description:
Lanzarote – This destination is one of the Canary Islands and is every bit the paradise it is known to be. Check out our guide to this natural beauty and find travel inspiration in spades. 

When ready, browse vacation packages to Lanzarote: https://www.expedia.com/Lanzarote.d282.Destination-Travel-Guides

The island oasis of #Lanzarote, Spain, is eagerly awaiting your arrival. Venture to the easternmost island of the Spanish archipelago and discover this scenic hot spot. With the help of artist and architect Cesar Manrique, Lanzarote’s landscape has integrated the natural beauty of the island with organic building designs. 

Kick-start your #vacation at the Cesar Manrique Foundation, which was once the home of the famous architect. You’ll come across rooms that are built into caves created by a volcano eruption long ago. Jameos del Agua is another fascinating attraction, where you can climb down the staircase into caves with restaurants and a concert venue. 

#Tour the fire mountains at Timanfaya National Park and marvel at the flames rising from the center of the earth or bask on the pristine shores of Playa del Carmen. Head to the rock pools at Punta Mujeres and go on a snorkeling excursion around the cove. 

For now, we hope you enjoy watching this #travel #guide as much as we enjoyed making it.

iXCW5t7asms.title: One Day in Phuket | Expedia
iXCW5t7asms.description:
A long layover in Phuket, Thailand, could mean a romp on the country’s largest island or an uneventful day at the airport. Skip waiting in the terminal; instead, tap into your adventurous side and hit the best Phuket beaches and attractions before boarding your next flight. 

Even just one day in Phuket provides you with the opportunity to revel in its tropical landscape. While you’re on the island, seek out the Big Buddha, a massive marble statue on the Naka Kerd Mountain, and cruise over to James Bond Island and Koh Panyee. For an adventure, charter a boat on Phang Nga Bay, or simply worship the sun on the shores of Kata or Surin Beach. If you’re still wondering what to see in Phuket, consider venturing to Khao Toh Sae in Phuket Town—which is home to hundreds of macaque monkeys—or relish the nightlife in Patong Beach. From the dazzling Phuket Fantasea to the emerald waters off the coast, you just might find yourself wishing for a flight delay. 

Explore Phuket in a day to get in touch with the island’s culture, cuisine, and coastlines. Even with just a few hours to spare, your island adventure will be well worth the layover.

bPvnwkqOZ_M.title: One Day in Kuala Lumpur | Expedia
bPvnwkqOZ_M.description:
Before you cozy up in the airport for a long layover in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, consider all the adventures you could have outside the terminal walls. Several hours is more than enough time to get a sense of the city, so instead of longingly looking out the airport windows, hail a cab and experience one day in Kuala Lumpur before your next flight.

The capital city is home to various things to do, from sightseeing to shopping. Begin your romp at the Petronas Twin Towers, where you can view the city from the observation deck and stroll across the Skybridge. If you’re ready for some retail therapy, head to the Central Market or the six-story Suria KLCC shopping mall. While exploring the town from top to bottom, climb the stairs to the temple in the Batu Caves, which is one of the most famous Hindu shrines outside of India, or picnic on the green lawns at Merdeka Square.

Whether you spend the day noshing on local cuisine or touring the Sultan Abdul Samad Building, 24 hours in Kuala Lumpur is sure to give you a sneak peek into “The Garden City of Lights.” Keep an eye on the time and soak up this destination before boarding your next flight.

jMl49tRN4kQ.title: One Day in Singapore | Expedia
jMl49tRN4kQ.description:
A long layover in Singapore is a blessing in disguise. With hours to go until your next flight, you have plenty of time to get out of the airport and explore the island country. Whether you have a full 24 hours in Singapore or just enough time for one sightseeing adventure, explore outside the terminal and get to know the Garden City. 

This tropical destination is known for its parks, so you might as well begin your romp at Gardens by the Bay. Look up and marvel at the towering, futuristic Supertrees, explore the tropical horticulture in the Bay South Garden, and venture around the greenhouses at the Flower Dome and the Cloud Forest. While you’re in town, you can’t miss the Merlion, the half-fish, half-lion statue that spits water into the Marina Bay, or the Singapore Flyer, the world’s largest observation wheel. If you still have time to spare, discover the captivating exhibits at the ArtScience Museum and attend a performance featuring authentic Singaporean dancers. 

Even if you can only spend one day in Singapore before catching your next flight, you’ll find countless ways to experience the city life. From strolling across the Helix Bridge to simply taking a seat by Marina Bay, you’ll be glad you ventured outside of the airport.
